<paragraph id="9C5CBB5CD211BD3453C6CF95EF8C95EA" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E3ED6B4EEB017C967280D44AF3CB10D8" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">
<taxonomicName id="09D13CDD6C7747BCBF4FAA18154D4837" authority="Balke, Bergsten &amp; Hendrich, 2017" authorityName="Balke, Bergsten &amp; Hendrich" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Rompindessus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rompindessus jenisi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenisi">Rompindessus jenisi</taxonomicName>
sp. n. by present designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D2D4C03027F70EB5399CA98E145D0A" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A032F06543A5A1978EEF096B24EBE53E" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="42DFEC076AC565D9111B4AAD2F49D084" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">
Of the set of structural features generally used to classify 
<taxonomicName id="59758E4AE122DB4FE3357A18B08B3C04" lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" rank="tribe" tribe="Bidessini">Bidessini</taxonomicName>
, the following combination is present in this taxon: 1) occipital line present; 2) basal pronotal striae present; 3) basal elytral striae absent; 4) sutural line on elytron absent; 5) basal epipleural transverse carina absent; 6) clypeus with thick anterior bead (or margin); 7) longitudinal elytral carina on disc absent; and 8) parameres two-segmented. Moreover, the male pro- and mesotarsus appear stout, and distinctly dilated laterally; the pronotum is comparably long and parallel-sided and the colour of beetle is conspicuously dark orange. This differentiates 
<taxonomicName id="49BD8DEF856D55291FDE070DC55AF5E1" authority="Balke, Bergsten &amp; Hendrich, 2017" authorityName="Balke, Bergsten &amp; Hendrich" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Rompindessus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rompindessus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Rompindessus</taxonomicName>
gen. n. from all other 
<taxonomicName id="3FCA60B25B66E41B27442772B53098CD" lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" rank="tribe" tribe="Bidessini">Bidessini</taxonomicName>
. In the key to 
<taxonomicName id="36F12614EC99941BECE2FCBF47066613" lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" rank="tribe" tribe="Bidessini">Bidessini</taxonomicName>
genera by 
<bibRefCitation id="AF1B8549BEDF504912881385ADCC1DB9" author="Miller, KB" journalOrPublisher="Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore" pageId="9" pageNumber="146" title="Diving Beetles of the World. Systematics and Biology of the Dytiscidae." year="2016">Miller and Bergsten (2016)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName id="42E02F34F2BE79BF7216D0F524CE06B4" authority="Balke, Bergsten &amp; Hendrich, 2017" authorityName="Balke, Bergsten &amp; Hendrich" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Rompindessus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rompindessus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Rompindessus</taxonomicName>
keys out to 
<taxonomicName id="FF473DDBC5485634DA04B26B3444445E" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Platydytes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platydytes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platydytes</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="8B469EC559170338FC08824807B908A0" originalValue="BistrÃ¶m">Bistroem</normalizedToken>
, 1988, which only occurs in sub-Saharan Africa. Apart from geography, 
<taxonomicName id="4863E057C405BC42E56DD910389742CA" authority="Balke, Bergsten &amp; Hendrich, 2017" authorityName="Balke, Bergsten &amp; Hendrich" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Rompindessus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rompindessus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Rompindessus</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="7A170C8BFB1D0E18DBAC5F3646C32428" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Platydytes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platydytes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platydytes</taxonomicName>
by the thickly bordered clypeal margin (finely bordered to indistinct in 
<taxonomicName id="A69D5BDADC1778AC77D8B2B376706B9E" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Platydytes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platydytes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platydytes</taxonomicName>
), the enlarged, laterally expanded male pro- and mesotarsomeres I-III, the dark orange colouration with dark speckles on elytra, and the more discontinuous body outline between pronotum and elytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B9FC5C2ADEF20B65417F3D30CC4EA03A" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="EF4B53A8004C5E5894D46E3FFBA8FA65" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2892DF3B842ECC6CA5FF9705970ACD5" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">
Named after the collecting locality, Rompin village, and the ending - dessus as used for many genera in 
<taxonomicName id="9C709FAFB451299F01C22F46D9AF945E" lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" rank="tribe" tribe="Bidessini">Bidessini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
